# Example Environment Variables Configuration
# Copy this file to '.env' in the root directory (if using a bundler like Webpack/Vite)
# OR simply use these keys in the extension's options page during runtime testing.

# Choose your preferred provider and input the API key below:

# 1. OPENAI
# Get an API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-proj-your_openai_api_key_here"

# 2. ANTHROPIC (CLAUDE)
# Get an API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-your_anthropic_api_key_here"

# 3. GOOGLE GEMINI
# Get an API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY="your_gemini_api_key_here"

# NOTE: Never commit actual API keys to GitHub or any public version control!
# Real API keys should be handled securely, ideally in an 'options.html' page 
# where the user inputs their own key, which is saved locally to their browser using chrome.storage.local.
